♪Time flies never to be recalled♪

5
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:22,700
♪When your smile is embedded
in the starry night♪

6
00:00:22,740 --> 00:00:25,740
♪We are puppets of twisted fates♪

7
00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:28,620
♪Constantly intertwining♪

8
00:00:28,660 --> 00:00:31,660
♪Dissolving in the crowd♪

9
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:34,940
♪Perhaps out of reach and out of sight♪

10
00:00:34,940 --> 00:00:37,260
♪Constantly flashing through my dreams♪

11
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:45,100
♪The sudden icy wind blurs my vision♪

12
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:50,660
♪The rain drew that day to an end♪

13
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:54,380
♪How I wish your beauty♪

14
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:59,460
♪I want to love you,
love you, love you, love you♪

15
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
[My Divine Emissary]

16
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,860
[Episode 18]

17
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:17,500
[Sai Residence]

18
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,040
Have some tea.

19
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:30,760
Huai'an.

20
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,200
Can you pinch me?

21
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:34,480
What's wrong?

22
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,920
I feel like everything right now

23
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,240
is just too good to be true.

24
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:41,280
It's almost like a dream.

25
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:43,160
Don't be silly.

26
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,480
All of this is real.

27
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,240
Besides,

28
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,560
our life will only get better.

29
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,280
I've been thinking,

30
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:56,760
once we reach the frontier,

31
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,480
we can build a little house.

32
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:01,600
That way, I can plant some flowers

33
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:02,880
or some plants in the yard.

34
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,160
Oh, and...

35
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:06,480
I also want to have a little dog too,

36
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,520
with a bell

37
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:09,560
around its neck,

38
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:11,480
jingling as it runs.

39
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:12,480
It's going to be so lively.

40
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,040
What do you think?

41
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,640
Whatever you say.

42
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,240
That's so boring.

43
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:21,840
You still haven't told me

44
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:24,240
what kind of life
you want in the future.

45
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,680
Everything you said just now

46
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,200
is exactly what I want.

47
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:35,600
Alright.

48
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,840
Then from now on,

49
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,640
we'll do things my way at home.

50
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:41,440
Okay.

51
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,000
Wan,

52
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,880
I still have some matters
to take care of in the capital.

53
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,760
Can you wait for me?

54
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,320
Wait for His Majesty
to return to the capital

55
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,560
to announce your sudden death news,

56
00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:00,580
then we'll have nothing to worry about.

57
00:03:03,460 --> 00:03:04,260
I'll wait for you.

58
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:05,660
Be careful.

59
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:07,700
Alright.

60
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:19,840
[Sai Residence]

61
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:24,020
Alright.

62
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:24,780
I've got to go now.

63
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:28,700
Your Majesty,

64
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,100
take care of Wan for me.

65
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:33,460
Don't worry.

66
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,420
I'll take good care of Wan.

67
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,740
Here's some food that I've
prepared for you to eat on the way.

68
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:43,140
Wan,

69
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,020
when I'm away,

70
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:45,780
could you...

71
00:03:45,780 --> 00:03:48,140
I'll stay at Sai Residence

72
00:03:48,140 --> 00:03:49,220
and not go anywhere.

73
00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:51,300
I won't let anyone find out about me.

74
00:03:51,780 --> 00:03:52,420
Your Grace.

75
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:54,220
It's getting late.

76
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:55,220
We should leave.

77
00:03:58,220 --> 00:03:58,980
I'm leaving now.

78
00:04:18,020 --> 00:04:18,860
Wait for me.

79
00:04:20,580 --> 00:04:21,260
I'll wait for you.

80
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:22,460
Don't get hurt.

81
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:36,460
Let's go!

82
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:38,500
Let's go!

83
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:38,900
Let's go!

84
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:40,900
Let's go!

85
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:53,300
[Sai Family Escort Agency]

86
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:54,600
It's raining.

87
00:04:54,960 --> 00:04:56,800
It hasn't rained
for a month in Yang City.

88
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,560
I thought

89
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,480
Yang City would
be as dry as the capital.

90
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,200
What is happening?

91
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:24,240
Am I having hallucinations?

92
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,120
Second Prince.

93
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:30,720
Second Prince.

94
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,720
The thing you asked me to investigate

95
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,720
has been clarified.

96
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,520
How is it?

97
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:34,760
The reason why

98
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,000
they could solve the drought problem

99
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:37,560
was because they've built a project

100
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,920
called the "Aqueduct".

101
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,680
It first started in Lu County.

102
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,320
It was managed
by a county official named Li Ming.

103
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:44,520
But regarding the details,

104
00:05:44,520 --> 00:05:45,800
I don't really know much.

105
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,040
Yes.

106
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,760
Aqueduct?

107
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:56,720
I heard there'll be a drama performance

108
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,960
at Qingteng Teahouse tonight.

109
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,880
Do you all want to go?

110
00:05:58,880 --> 00:05:59,920
A drama performance?

111
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:01,720
Do you want to watch?

112
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,160
If you want, we can go together tonight.

113
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,080
That's alright.

114
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,400
I was just thinking about the time

115
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,280
I used to go watch
dramas when I was a kid,

116
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,600
but I always fell asleep

117
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,880
before they finished.

118
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:17,120
Your Majesty.

119
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,200
Minister Li is here.

120
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:22,600
Your Majesty.

121
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,360
Minister Li.

122
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,840
Did everything go smoothly
on the way here?

123
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,320
Reporting to Your Majesty,

124
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,280
everything went smoothly.

125
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,280
It's just that the continuous rain

126
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:32,960
made the road hard to travel across.

127
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,480
That's why we were
delayed for a few days.

128
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,120
Minister Li.

129
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,280
How have you been recently?

130
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,000
Why do you look so much leaner?

131
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,520
His Majesty found me a great place

132
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,920
with a beautiful scenery.

133
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,040
It's really comfortable there.

134
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,160
That's great.

135
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,720
Minister Li.

136
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,320
This is Wan,

137
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,000
whom you know.

138
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,360
Greetings to Your Highness.

139
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:51,960
Minister Li.

140
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:53,720
And he,

141
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,880
is Ximi's second prince, Li Tao.

142
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:56,800
Your Grace.

143
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:58,200
You're Minister Li, the one building

144
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,240
the aqueduct in Lu County, right?

145
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,320
Yes, Your Grace.

146
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,560
Can you show me the blueprints

147
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,360
of the aqueduct works?

148
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,440
Well...

149
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:04,320
No, no.

150
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,400
It's alright, Minister Li.

151
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:05,920
Ignore him.

152
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:06,480
Mengmeng.

153
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,160
But I really need to...

154
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,960
This is the eldest daughter
of the Sai Family Escort Agency,

155
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:11,640
Sai Xue.

156
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,320
Miss Sai.

157
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:14,960
This is Minister Li.

158
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,280
He will be staying
in Yang City in the future.

159
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,600
You'll be assisting him

160
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,800
with the matters
related to the watercourse.

161
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:22,040
But regarding his identity,

162
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,560
I'll need you to keep it a secret.

163
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:24,880
I understand.

164
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,040
Minister Li.

165
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,520
Feel free to let me know
if you need anything.

166
00:07:29,520 --> 00:07:30,200
Minister Li.

167
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,920
Please sit down and eat with us.

168
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,840
I already ate on the way.

169
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,480
Then you can go with Lu Huan

170
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,680
to the residence first.

171
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:40,600
Minister Li, please.

172
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,080
I'm full.

173
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:48,040
You guys enjoy your meal.

174
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,360
Minister Li.

175
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,040
Minister Li, wait.

176
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,280
Miss Mengmeng.

177
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:00,720
Do you need anything?

178
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,440
Minister Li.

179
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:04,080
There's a drama performance
at the teahouse tonight.

180
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,640
Would you like to go together?

181
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,560
That would be my honor.

182
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:11,880
What?

183
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:13,360
Do you want to go too?

184
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,560
Minister Li, please.

185
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,560
Minister Li.

186
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,240
Please.

187
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,840
Miss Mengmeng.

188
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,480
How did you know I like watching drama?

189
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:52,040
Bravo!

190
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,720
Come on. Let's go home.

191
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:05,920
Sweet pea,

192
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:06,920
you're awake.

193
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,080
Dad,

194
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,600
is the drama over?

195
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,360
Not yet.

196
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,880
Sorry, Dad.

197
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:15,160
The drama made me so sleepy.

198
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,560
I couldn't help falling asleep
as soon as they started singing.

199
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,520
It's okay.

200
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,840
Daddy will take you home to sleep.

201
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,080
Next time, I will definitely
finish watching it with Daddy.

202
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,160
I won't sleep.

203
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,720
You promise?

204
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:32,320
- Pinky promise.
- Pinky promise for a hundred years.

205
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:42,220
Bravo!

206
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,760
Nope.

207
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:44,720
I surely won't fall asleep.

208
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,600
I definitely, definitely
won't sleep this time.

209
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,440
I must finish watching with him.

210
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,520
Why are you here?

211
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,680
Yeah, why are you here?

212
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,000
Stay down.

213
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:17,680
You're blocking me.

214
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,400
Mengmeng.

215
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,440
Didn't you say you didn't want to come?

216
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,600
How come you came without telling me?

217
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,640
You watched dramas with other man.

218
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,120
Would you care to explain?

219
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,600
You're sitting in my seat. Get up.

220
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,600
Does it have your name written on it?

221
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,480
First come, first served.

222
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,280
This is Minister Li's seat.

223
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,360
Greetings to both masters.

224
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:38,960
Minister Li.

225
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,680
- Sir, you have a seat.
- Please, have a seat.

226
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,200
I'll sit in the back.

227
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:40,920
You sit, you sit.

228
00:10:42,720 --> 00:10:44,320
Minister Li, ignore them. Please sit.

229
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,560
Well, then, thank you.

230
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,280
Since Mengmeng has said so,

231
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:49,480
I'll sit in the back then.

232
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:50,320
It's alright, Minister Li.

233
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:50,960
Please enjoy.

234
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,920
Master Li,

235
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:52,720
please.

236
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,040
You...

237
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,200
Are you trying to mess
with me on purpose?

238
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:05,040
I don't even take you seriously.

239
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,600
Why would I do that?

240
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,440
Is that so?

241
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,280
Then why do I smell a strong scent

242
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,600
of jealousy every day?

243
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:10,640
Keep it down, keep it down.

244
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:11,560
What's with the noise?

245
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,160
Exactly, what's with the noise?

246
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,720
Why all this fuss is about?

247
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,160
Where did these rude men come from?

248
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:16,720
If you're not watching
the show, get out.

249
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,160
Out!

250
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:25,600
It's all your fault.

251
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:28,680
Has she...

252
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:29,800
been influenced by Sai Xue lately?

253
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,560
Why is she so mean?

254
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:33,360
I think she's quite cute.

255
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:36,120
I'm really sorry.

256
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,600
I still couldn't let you

257
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,680
finish watching the drama.

258
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,160
Some things,

259
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,920
are destined not to be perfect.

260
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,320
Don't dwell too much on the outcome,

261
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:53,080
the journey is more important.

262
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,440
As long as there are beautiful moments
along the way,

263
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,520
that's good enough.

264
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,760
It's like us
watching the show together today.

265
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,320
Minister Li.

266
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:11,360
What kind of person
do you hope Wanwan will become

267
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,600
when she grows up?

268
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,240
As long as Wanwan

269
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:20,320
can grow up safely and happily,

270
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,720
that's all I ask for.

271
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:25,440
Alright.

272
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,120
Wait.

273
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:53,280
Let's go.

274
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,280
I...

275
00:12:57,280 --> 00:12:57,960
Run!

276
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:02,680
Go!

277
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,600
Be careful.

278
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,600
Miss Li.

279
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:51,840
Dad.

280
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:03,760
Are you...Are you hurt?

281
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,240
I'm fine.

282
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,360
How about you?

283
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:08,680
Does it hurt?

284
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,440
I'm fine. I'm fine.

285
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,960
I'm fine.

286
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:20,920
Wanwan.

287
00:14:25,560 --> 00:14:26,720
Don't cry.

288
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:39,960
Dad.

